## Key Business Logic
- No usage limits enforced in frontend — users can scan unlimited times
- Auth: wx.login + getUserInfo cloud function → openid
- Multi-page menu: up to 6 photos per session
- Image compression: wx.compressImage (quality 50, width 960) before upload
- Expand/collapse: tap dish card to toggle detail, pure frontend
- Category filter: inferDishCategory (沙拉/意面/牛排/披萨/汤品/海鲜/鸡肉/甜点/饮品/其他)
- Order summary: add/decrease per dish, order bar, order detail panel with scroll-to-dish
- OCR price extraction: extractPricesFromOcrText + applyPricesByIndex for multi-column menus

## Vant Components Used
van-button, van-cell, van-cell-group, van-icon, van-image, van-loading, van-toast, van-empty, van-tag, van-action-sheet, van-overlay

## Don'ts
- No cross-platform frameworks (Taro, uni-app)
- No unnecessary npm packages
- No direct AI API calls from frontend (must go through cloud functions)
- No mock data or placeholder content — connect to real APIs
- No review/rating/social features (not in MVP)
- No image generation features (not in MVP)
- No localStorage for important data (use cloud database)
